page.title: 17WILDLIFE
page.content: There are three main types of habitat in this D-block: heathland,coniferous woodland pasture interspersed with deciduous woods.Few people live here,much of the area is used by the army,on the edge of the adjacent town it is used for recreation. Roe deer are in Yateley Heath Wood where periodically a cull is necessary if the numbers are too great.In all the woods there are grey squirrels and foxes.Foxes are also found in the gorseareas of the heaths.Smaller mammals e.g.voles and hedgehogs live in banks and hedges. A variety of birds and insects exist.Canada geese are winter migrants.see{LAKE}.Great Bramshot Farm is run as a nature reserve to demonstrate that modern farming can be compatible with keeping habitats.
